Citation.sTitle: Experimental Investigation of the Influence of NaCl on the Vapor-Liquid Equilibrium of CH3OH + H2O
Citation.sAbstract: New experimental results for the vapor-liquid equilibrium of the system sodium chloride + methanol + water are presented at (salt-free) solvent mixture methanol mole fractions from about 0.03 to 0.54, at sodium chloride molalities up to about 5.4 mol.kg-1 of the solvent mixture (but always below the solubility limit of the salt), at temperatures from about (313 to 397) K, and at total pressures from about (10 to 500) kPa.
